# {{ project_name }} — GitHub Copilot instructions

The canonical agent rules live in [AGENTS.md](../AGENTS.md). Read it first;
the notes below are Copilot-specific supplements only.

## Copilot-specific notes

- **Enumerate before guessing.** `verify-kit list-checks` lists every check
  this project knows about; `verify-kit describe <name>` shows its JSON
  Schema. Use these instead of inferring check names from prose.

- **`just verify` is the pre-commit gate.** Always run it before suggesting a
  change is complete. The `--quick` flag (`just verify --quick`) runs the fast
  slice (lint + typecheck + smoke) for in-editor iteration; the full command
  is what CI runs.

- **GitHub Actions CI runs the same `just verify`.** `.github/workflows/ci.yml`
  shells out to `just verify` — no Copilot suggestion should require steps that
  don't already pass that command locally. If CI fails but `just verify` passes
  locally, the answer is almost always "match the CI Python/Node version pinned
  by `.mise.toml`."

